Many people still believe that learning Linux is difficult, or that only experts can understand how a Linux system works. 
Though there is a lot of free documentation available, the documentation is widely scattered on the Web, and often 

confusing, since it is usually oriented toward experienced UNIX or Linux users. Today, thanks to the advancements in 

development, Linux has grown in popularity both at home and at work. The goal of this guide is to show people of all ages 
that Linux can be simple and fun, and used for all kinds of purposes.

许多人仍然相信学习Linux是困难的，或者说，只有专家才能理解Linux系统是如何工作的。虽然有很多免费的文档可用，文档是广泛分布

在网络上，而且经常混淆，因为它通常是面向有经验的UNIX或Linux用户。今天，由于在发展中不断进步，Linux已经在国内和在工作中越

来越流行。本指南的目的是要表明，Linux可以是简单和乐趣，并用于各种目的，所有年龄的人。
